The coffee menu is very reduced and put together for adults who would like to slow down and enjoy their cup of coffee in a quiet environment. We kindly ask you to consider this when you bring in children. Also, for safety reasons children cannot walk around without parental guidance.

fields.name: Bonanza Coffee Heroes
fields.description: Opened all the way back in 2007, Bonanza is one of the stalwarts of coffee culture in Berlin. Queues are common, especially on Sundays when the flea market is on at Mauerpark, but it’s worth the wait (and normally not that long anyway). Space is limited because they have to make room for the coffee roasters, but what other cafe can you name that roasts their own coffee on the premises?

fields.name: Five Elephant
fields.description: Five Elephant, that’s who. On top of having their own roasters, their beans are also direct trade, meaning they deal on a one-to-one basis with the growers. Five Elephant also scores points for its seclusion, at the far end of Reichenberger Straße, which means that most of the customers are from the neighbourhood and it’s never too packed.
